Creating Chart Visualization 15

Steps for Creating Avg Rental Price Vs YOYhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zHzSBNES6jE

1. Go to visualization and select Line and Stacked  Column Chart Visual

2. Go to the Dim Table on the field pane and drag and drop Month and Date name on the Shared Axis

3.. Go to the field pane and drag and drop Avg Price on the Column Values and YOY on the Line Values

4. Go to Format Pane and turn legend and title on, Style should be markers only and position should be Top

5. Turn Y axis. on,  Turn Gridlines on and change your color to gray and line style dashed and also turn on your Align Zeros

6. Go to Data Colors and  make YOY  blue, Data Labels should be turned on with color black

7. Go to title and turn it on, under Title Text, type Avg Rental Price vs YOY, Font color is black while background color is white and align center

8. Turn border on and make  its color white, Turn Visual Hearder on and make its color white


Steps for Creating Avg  Price by Neighborhood_group

1. Go to visualization and select ArgGIS chart Visual

2.. Go to the field pane and drag and drop Avg Price by Neighborhood_group on Location, Avg Rental Price on Color and lastly AvgPriceYOYGrowth on the Tooltips

3. Go to Format Pane and on title  type Layers and turn  show layers on,  Also turn Border on and make the color white

4. Go to title and turn it on, under Title Text, type Avg  Price by Neighborhood_group, Font color is black while background color is white and align center

5 Turn border on and make  its color white, Turn Visual Hearder on and make its background  color white border color white and icon color black. Turn Shadow on with color black and its position to be outside and preset to bottom right
